tuning_runs.notes: FAILED: Score worse (-0.0189) and over budget (+10.1 min). Greedy selects fewer diverse candidates.

conclusion: FAILED - Greedy selection produced worse results than simple sort+filter. Fewer samples got 3 candidates (64/80 vs ~70-75). RMSE was also worse.
key_finding: The simple baseline approach (sort by RMSE, filter by dissimilarity) is actually optimal. Greedy selection that considers combined score performs worse.
